comment: Johnson (BOS) beats Diaw (SAS) to the spot and gives him room to avoid the screen.
Diaw (SAS) holds Johnson (BOS) and affects his ability to secure the rebound.
Parker (SAS) does not affect Thomas' (BOS) ability to land. After Thomas comes to the floor, he pulls Parker to the ground as he falls on his own.
Thomas (BOS) tips the ball out of bounds.
Duncan (SAS) extends both arms into Bradley (BOS) and affects his movement through the screen.
Bradley (BOS) slides into Ginobili (SAS) and affects his movement.
Parker (SAS) makes incidental contact with Thomas (BOS) that does not cause the loss of control.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Green (SAS) was the shooter was upheld.
Ginobili (SAS) is in a legal guarding position when contact with Thomas (BOS) occurs.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court of a three point basket was upheld.
Thomas (BOS) commits a take foul on Leonard (SAS).
